=head1 DESCRIPTION

Specifies the Capacity Reservation targeting option of an Amazon EC2
instance.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 CapacityReservationPreference => Str

Indicates the instance's Capacity Reservation preferences. If equal to
C<open>, the instance can run in any open Capacity Reservation that has
matching attributes (instance type, platform, Availability Zone). If
equal to C<none>, the instance avoids running in a Capacity Reservation
even if one is available. The instance runs in On-Demand capacity.


=head2 CapacityReservationTarget => L<Paws::SecurityHub::AwsEc2LaunchTemplateDataCapacityReservationSpecificationCapacityReservationTargetDetails>

